description: A 2.3 magnitude earthquake hit Victoria's Mornington Peninsula on Saturday. The Bureau of Meteorology says there is no tsunami threat for Australia's coasts as a result of the earthquake.

title: Major League Eater James Webb funnels down nearly SIXTY donuts in eight minutes
description: James Webb, a competitor on the Major League Eating circuit, set a new world record after devouring 59 and a half donuts in eight minutes at a competition in San Diego on Friday.

title: Mum's horror diagnosis when egg-sized mass was discovered in her brain after a beauty treatment
description: Skye Hamilton, 27, was rushed to the hospital in Western Sydney six months ago where doctors were only able to remove some of the tumour - as taking it all away would have caused paralysis.

title: Melbourne man with DANOUT numberplates attacking Dan Andrews loses VicRoads appeal
description: Melbourne tradie Peter Dunlevie recently lost his appeal and was told he had until this Monday to hand the plates to VicRoads or his vehicle registration would be suspended and cancelled.

title: Coles, Woolworths: duopoly between supermarket giants causing spikes in grocery costs
description: The duopoly between Coles and Woolworths are key reasons why prices for groceries have increased, former ACCC Chair Rod Sims says, as the supermarket giants are accused of 'greed'.

title: Husband slaps man at Baltimore science conference for 'sexually assaulting his wife seven years ago'
description: During a Baltimore, Maryland medical conference a disturbing incident unfolded as an enraged husband confronted and physically assaulted a doctor on the podium.

title: Riley Gaines backs DeSantis for 2024 at rally as she tells crowd he's the 'right thing for women'
description: The outspoken advocate for protecting women's rights in sports spoke to a DeSantis rally in South Carolina, earlier tonight and said it was 'imperative' that his administration lead the country.

title: 'Drunk' and 'aggressive' woman on flight from LA to Las Vegas screams at passengers as she's removed
description: A 'drunk' and 'aggressive' woman who was onboard a flight from Los Angeles to Las Vegas screamed at other passengers as she was ordered off the plane over disorderly behavior.

title: Mullumbimby caravan near Byron Bay shows Australia's rental crisis has hit a new low
description: A rental for two caravans with an open lounge and kitchen 'covered and protected from the weather' by a roof and tarps in Mullumbimby in the Bryon Shire was posted to social media.

title: Florida neighborhood is at war after they catch local man on video admitting he traps cats
description: A Florida man has caused outrage in his neighborhood because he proudly traps stray cats that drift onto his property, never to be seen again.

title: Melbourne teen stabbed on bus in Preston a fortnight after Pasawm Lyhym died in Sunshine
description: Two teens were on board a bus in Preston in Melbourne's north-east on Friday when they became embroiled in an altercation.

title: Coronavirus concerns for fifth wave in Australia with 28 per cent monthly increase in case numbers
description: Experts have warned about a fifth wave of Covid hitting Australia, with a 28 per cent rise in case numbers driving a 'significant' increase in  Aussie workers taking sick leave.

title: Pre-marriage parties can come with a financial hangover of up to £1,200
description: Survey found men splash out more celebrating their friends' imminent nuptials - £920 on average for a UK stag weekend, compared with women spending £652 for a hen celebration.

title: Was Our Man In Washington involved in a 'SEX FOR SCOOPS' affair with a glamorous TV journalist?
description: Before dawn on October 13, 2020, no fewer than 14 officers from the Metropolitan Police's counter-terrorism unit slip through the front door of a block of flats on side street in central Westminster.

title: JAN MOIR: Phillip Schofield wasted no time in playing the victim
description: JAN MOIR: Schofield looked much diminished in his interview with Amol Rajan. Yet despite his crestfallen and haggard demeanour, he wasted no time in establishing his victim credentials.

title: This is why there's NO WAY Holly Willoughby will be forced out if ITV bosses stay put
description: Smiling among the top brass at the 2018 National Television awards was a handsome twentysomething assistant - as we now know, this was Schofield's much younger lover at the time.

title: Former owner of boat after the deaths of two children in Bournemouth says area is 'dangerous'
description: A girl of 12 and a boy of 17 were pulled from the sea after 'getting into difficulties' on Wednesday and died in hospital. Peter Lamb, 70, said the sea surrounding the pier was 'dangerous' for swimmers.

title: As she turns 90, actress SHEILA HANCOCK passes judgment on everything from Covid to cancel culture
description: SHEILA HANCOCK: I confess that nowadays I am sometimes nervous of expressing an opinion. Because of the threat of being 'cancelled'. That word sounds so terrifying. Erased from life.

title: A 'substantial number' of jobs in the civil service are under threat from AI robots
description: A Whitehall document predicted automation will spell the end of junior back-office roles with 'no citizen interaction' in the near future.

title: Scottish woman FINALLY becomes a mother at 53 after 25 years of trying
description: Helen Dalglish had endured 21 gruelling rounds of treatment at a cost of almost £100,000. She gave birth to her 'miracle' baby at the age of 53, after 25 years of failed fertility procedures.

title: Dead body of missing man, 35, was mistaken for a horror film prop
description: Ian Roberts, 35, was found hanging in the vehicle in a compound in Warrington but a witness didn't report his death as he believed the body was a 'dummy.'

title: Teenager, 19, charged with eight terror offences after bomb disposal squad raids his home
description: Detectives said self-radicalised Matthew King, 19, was a day away from launching an assault on a police station or army barracks after spending weeks conducting reconnaissance.

title: Watching medical dramas like Casualty could increase people's trust in real-life doctors
description: Regular exposure 'leads to increased PSR between audience members and physicians in medical dramas, which increases audience trust in real-life physicians'.

title: Airlines accused of fuelling Britain's child obesity epidemic by packing inflight meals with sugar
description: A Mail investigation has found that meals offered to children by easyJet, Jet 2, TUI and British Airways contain up to 16 teaspoons of sugar.

title: Natalee Holloway murder suspect Joran van der Sloot is en route to the United States
description: Joran van der Sloot is en route to the United States after the extradition process got underway Friday night in Peru.

title: TOM LEONARD investigates the truth about Sister Wilhelmina
description: TOM LEONARD: When nuns opened her coffin, all of Sister Wilhelmina was there, her body - which the nuns insist hadn't been embalmed or preserved - showing almost no signs of decomposition.

title: Ioan Gruffudd's daughter, 13, has filed for a restraining order against her FATHER
description: In documents filed on May 31 at the Los Angeles Superior Court, 13-year-old Ella Evans applied for a temporary restraining order from her 49-year-old dad.

title: Tropical Storm Arlene, the first named storm of the hurricane season, forms in the Gulf of Mexico
description: In an advisory issued on Friday, the National Hurricane Center announced they had had named the storm as Arlene, which was 240 miles west of Fort Myers, Florida.

title: The View is thrashed in scathing New York Times review by longtime fan and author Megan Stack
description: The View has been thrashed in a scathing New York Times review by longtime fan and author Megan Stack who called it a 'chorus of conformity'.

title: How I exposed the DARK SIDE of Facebook: FRANCES HAUGEN hired to police fake news on the site
description: FRANCES HAUGEN: After more than two years of working for Facebook, in a bid to expose some of those emerging dangers, I decided to become a whistleblower.

title: Major travel delays for morning commuters as thick fog blankets city
description: Fog has blanketed Sydney causing disruption to early morning ferry trips and other transport.
